<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Service (1991) - VALVE TRAIN: CAMSHAFT, HYDRAULIC VALVE LIFTERS AND PUSH RODS -
        CAMSHAFT ASSEMBLY - FUEL PUMP CAM REMOVAL
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="2">
        <title>FUEL PUMP CAM REMOVAL</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The camshaft gear, spacer and fuel pump cam eccentric can be removed without removing the
                    camshaft. This is accomplished as follows:
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Visually inspect the fuel pump cam for wear or scoring, prior to removal.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the camshaft Allen screw,
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e435_71.xml" xrefid="ef4350410">4.10</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the prior camshaft gear with gear puller holes using
                <emph type="bold">ZTSE2295-69</emph>
                Puller,
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350416">4.16</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach the vibration damper, crank and cam gear remover
                <emph type="bold">ZTSE2295-69</emph>
                (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350416">4.16</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ) to the cam gear using two bolts threaded through the long slots in the puller plate. Use the small
                shaft protector and position it on the end of the cam shaft. Turn the forcing screw (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350416">4.16</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ) to remove the gear.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The new cam gear w/counterweight lug and gear puller holes remover can not use the current
                tool
                <emph type="bold">ZTSE2295-69</emph>. The new gear can be removed using any common three-jaw pressure
                screw puller [which has a spreader for the jaws]. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350417">4.17</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <figure id="ef4350416" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg14739a" filename="../figcg1/CG14739A.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.16 Removing Camshaft Gear Using ZTSE-2295-69</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4350417" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg14741" filename="../figcg1/CG14741.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.17 Removing New Camshaft Gear Using Typical Three Jaw Puller</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the gear removed, remove the woodruff key on the camshaft, near the fuel pump cam using
                <emph type="bold">SE4156</emph>
                Puller
                <emph type="bold"></emph>(
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e435_77.xml" xrefid="ef4350418">4.18</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove thrust flange spacer using
                <emph type="bold">SE4156</emph>
                Puller (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e435_77.xml" xrefid="ef4350419">4.19</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
